
[1]foreclose

   FORECLO'SE, v.t. s as z. To shut up; to preclude; to stop; to prevent.

   The embargo with Spain foreclosed this trade.

   To foreclose a mortgager, in law, is to cut him off from his equity of
   redemption, or the power of redeeming the mortgaged premises, by a
   judgment of court.

   [To foreclose a mortgage is not technically correct, but is often
   used.]
